+### Bucket E — Boot-order bridge (500ms DOMContentLoaded timeout)
+
+Status:
+
+- **watch / low-risk held** — downgraded from blocker after boot timing proof (2026-04-23).
+- Timeout may remain as a harmless bridge. Removal is optional cleanup, not required progress.
+
+Proof result (2026-04-23):
+
+- Dev-only `_bootProbe` harness added to `shell.js` (localStorage-gated, removable).
+- Measured on a cold-boot run: shell policy listener attached at ~353ms; first `rc:runtime-policy-changed` event received at ~420ms; 500ms timeout fired at ~853ms.
+- Shell attached its listener before state.js fired the initial policy event in all tested boot paths. The timeout did not catch a missed event — the listener caught it.
+- Conclusion: proof showed shell attached before first policy event in tested boot paths; timeout appears redundant for initial policy capture, but may remain temporarily as a harmless bridge until a separate optional cleanup pass retires it.
+
+Remaining note:
+
+- The timeout also calls `window.rcTheme.syncShellState()` and `window.rcAppearance.syncButtons()`, which the `rc:runtime-policy-changed` listener does not. If the timeout is ever retired, those two calls must move into the event listener or find another dispatch path before removal.
+- This is not a current blocker. It is a note for the optional cleanup pass.
+
+---
+
+### Bucket F — Pricing opener provenance (billing.js follow-up slice)
+
+Status:
+
+- blocked pending Central authorization for a Station 2 follow-up slice scoping `js/billing.js`.
+
+Problem:
+
+- `getActiveModalReport()` and `getPricingSurfaceReport()` in `shell.js` report pricing opener as inferred generics (`'pricing'`, `'unknown'`, `'pending-paid-intent'`), not truthful provenance.
+- `billing.js` entry points `openPricingForSignup()`, `openPricingForAccount()`, and `showPricingForGatedAction()` do not write a shared opener context that shell can read.
+- `openPricingForSignup()` and `openPricingForAccount()` clear pending plan on entry, so pending-plan state is not a reliable provenance substitute.
+
+Protection rule:
+
+- Do not treat current shell inference as provenance. Do not normalize `getActiveModalReport().opener` by adding more shell-side guessing.
+
+Retirement condition:
+
+- Central authorizes a Station 2 follow-up slice that includes `js/billing.js` in scope.
+- A single readable pricing-open context is defined and written from the three legitimate billing entry points only: opener name, allowed surface, message/source, timestamp or session token.
+- Shell reads that context from billing rather than inferring from side effects.
+- Acceptance requires runtime test with probes.
+
+---
+
